monitors.description:
**Keeping this silent. Once deployment is complete, will remove BatchEventHub from the dimension

This tracks successful notification time for batch notifications in partial sync.
Right now this will only trigger sev3 when there is no batch notification processing for 10 mins.
fires with abnormal volume of full sync notifications.
Messages in the queue have already waited 10 hours (36M milliseconds)

customLinks.serverQuery:
where activityName == "PartialSyncIngestionJob.ExecuteInternalWithInputAsync"
where properties.contains("RetryNotificationPriority=[Arm]")
let metricValueStr = Regex.Match(properties, "MetricValue=\[([^\]]+)\]").Groups[1].Value
where metricValueStr != null && metricValueStr != ""
let delayMs = Int32.Parse(metricValueStr)
where delayMs > 30000

customLinks.title: Notifications out of SLA

monitors.description:
Run this for more details of specific failures causes

let startTime = datetime(2020-04-15 15:00:00.0000);
let endTime = datetime(2020-04-15 18:00:00.0000);
let delayInSec = 30;               
ARG_NotificationState| where TIMESTAMP > startTime  and TIMESTAMP < endTime and Environment != "eus2euap"
| where SuccessfulIngestionTime != ""
| project notificationStartTime = todatetime(StartTimeInUtc), notificationIngestionTime = todatetime(SuccessfulIngestionTime), notificationSubId = SubscriptionId, notificationResourceId = ResourceId, TaskName, FailureReason 
| where notificationResourceId !contains "Microsoft.Authorization/roleAssignments" and notificationResourceId contains "providers"
and notificationResourceId !contains "Security/pricings" and notificationResourceId !contains("routetables")
| extend delay = todouble(notificationIngestionTime - notificationStartTime) /10000000
| project delay, sub = tolower(extract("/subscriptions/(.*?)/",1,notificationResourceId)), type =  tolower(extract("providers(/.*?/.*?/).*",1,notificationResourceId)), notificationStartTime, notificationIngestionTime, notificationResourceId, FailureReason
| where sub != "c986b13b-e2c1-4852-9628-5de8ebbb023e" and sub != "97eb8a33-7802-4a2e-b051-771e90e3283b" 
| where notificationStartTime > startTime
| summarize count() by bin(notificationStartTime,5m), FailureReason
| render timechart

Fires with abnormal volume of full sync notifications.
Advisor at present sends all their data every 4hrs, hence the time period.

Tracks PS time to ingest a notification to queue to kusto dm queue
If average time =0, means nothing is being processed. Upper limit is of 30s.

customLinks.serverQuery:
where activityName == "PartialSyncIngestionJob.ExecuteInternalWithInputAsync"
where properties.contains("RetryQueuePriority=[Arm]")
let metricValueStr = Regex.Match(properties, "MetricValue=\[([^\]]+)\]").Groups[1].Value
where metricValueStr != null && metricValueStr != ""
let metricValue = Int32.Parse(metricValueStr)
where metricValue > 30000
